
1. Install it with asdf-install or using symlink to .asd file.

2. Also you have to install JDK to be able to run local matches

3. Write your bot instead of random one in "MyBot.lisp".

4. Build an executable: simply run "./my-bot" in the directory with .asd)

5. Test it locally against one of the example bots: "./run-match DualBot" (or any other bot in example_bots)

6. For running MyBot at the server the code should be slightly modified

7. I'm not sure if common-lisp bot is able to be run at the server just now, but soon it will be
